Heinz baby food batches were recalled due to potential lead contamination.
Similarly, meat products from Thorn Apple Valley and Sara Lee were recalled for Listeria concerns.
The outbreaks have raised questions about food safety regulations and the need for stricter enforcement.
Listeria can be deadly, especially for vulnerable populations.
The recalls highlight the importance of proper food handling and cooking to prevent illness.
The ongoing efforts to contain outbreaks emphasize the role of consumers in ensuring food safety.
The recalls serve as a reminder of the risks associated with foodborne pathogens like E. coli and Listeria.
